lead_paragraph: Alphabet, the parent company of Google, said on Friday that it planned to cut 12,000 jobs, becoming the latest technology company to reduce its work force because of concerns about a broader economic slowdown, after a hiring spree during the pandemic.

abstract: Repercussions from an attack on the bridge between Crimea and Russia.
snippet: Repercussions from an attack on the bridge between Crimea and Russia.
lead_paragraph: A fireball consumed two sections of the only bridge linking the occupied Crimean Peninsula to Russia on Saturday, disrupting the most important supply line for Russian troops fighting in southern Ukraine. The attack dealt an embarrassing  if mostly symbolic  blow to the Kremlin, which is facing continued losses on the battlefield and mounting criticism at home.

snippet: The decision is a big victory for the families of the 29 people who died in the attack in August 1998, four months after the signing of the Good Friday Agreement.
lead_paragraph: LONDON  Nearly 25 years after a car bomb killed 29 people in the Northern Ireland town of Omagh  the deadliest single attack of the era known as the Troubles  the British government said on Thursday that it would open an independent inquiry into whether security forces could have averted the bombing.
